<p>You have gone past your <b>first 6 months.</b><br>
Your best course of action is to contact the seller. You should discuss the longevity of your product.<br>
If so, you may still be entitled to a refund, repair, or replacement or exchange. It is unlikely, that if this is the case, the seller will give you a refund.<br> They are likely to give you a part refund, depending how much you have used the product.
Please return your item as soon as possible to, your consumer rights last up to 6 years.<br>
The seller can ask you to prove that you did not cause the fault yourself. It is best to get some advice from a local trade association or approved trader.</p>